# Purpose

Enforce the boundary between the two packages in this monorepo. Package-specific folder structure, dependency direction, and module conventions are in `backend/architecture.mdc` and `frontend/architecture.mdc`.

# Rules

## Monorepo Structure

```
fullstack-authentication/
├── backend/   Express + MongoDB API (Node.js, TypeScript)
└── frontend/  React + Vite SPA (TypeScript)
```

- There is NO shared package between backend and frontend.
- DO NOT import code across package boundaries.
- Each package manages its own `node_modules`, `tsconfig.json`, and scripts.

## Package Responsibilities

| Package | Role |
|---|---|
| `backend/` | REST API, authentication, job scheduling, SSE, MongoDB data access |
| `frontend/` | Browser SPA, UI rendering, state management, API consumption |

# Anti-Patterns

- DO NOT import from `backend/` inside `frontend/` source, or vice versa.
- DO NOT introduce a shared `packages/` directory without updating both `tsconfig.json` files and all import aliases.
